RenoRun is one of its kind when it comes to innovation. We are all at once a tech company, retail company and construction materials company. In short, we harness the power of data and technology to streamline building supply, with the convenience of online shopping. Our goal is to ease the purchasing process for construction workers, and save them loads of time from all the back and forth from the construction site. We do this by providing a platform where they can buy materials online, set up the time and day they would like their materials to be delivered, and voila!
The Data team is growing, and we are looking for a
BI Developer
to hop on the bandwagon. This dream team is responsible for delivering complex projects in various areas including operations, finance, marketing, product, customer service, and engineering to name a few. Our purpose is to help make impactful, smart decisions across RenoRun by providing Data Input, Data Output, and Data Culture. Your challenge will be to deliver well tested, up to date and documented data to provide accurate and informative data value to all internal clients.
You'll be an integral part of connecting the team to the business and ensuring a win-win for all!
Note: This is a hybrid role in Montreal &/ Toronto.
What you'll do:
Help build and maintain data pipelines and infrastructure by extracting, transforming, and loading data into the cloud-based data warehouse (Snowflake);
Work closely with internal clients to understand their data needs and build out the required solutions;
Clean and transform raw data into business logic to help stakeholders build reports, and make sure the right data is getting to the right people at the right time;
Look for ways to refactor and improve the modelling and data pipelines to reflect reality and increase efficiency;
